  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is typically defined as the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, often by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Key elements generally include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's source\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money back into the economy as seemingly legitimate funds\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most laws consider it a criminal offense involving financial transactions intended to hide the proceeds of criminal activity.",
